msContents.summary: Contains glosses on Yevamot and Ḳidushin.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 31; written lines: 31; Uniform layout. Chapter titles written in larger characters. Hard-point ruling visible. Catchwords on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Italian cursive script of the 18th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Tosaphoth al Yebhamoth ve-Kiddushin. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional Ms. 26,915.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 24: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153: inscribed, folio [138v].
